    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="425"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Dupuy de Lôme</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Legation</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: On my return to my house I find a
                    telegram from the Spanish consul at Key West, confirming the press report of the
                    return of six of the Cubans who left Key West on the 7th instant, <pb
                        facs="0462" n="1196" xml:id="pg_1196"/> the day of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >George W. Childs</hi> expedition. The consul informs me that it is said
                    there are more concealed in the surrounding keys, and among them one of the
                    leaders, Serafin Sanchez. If they were rescued by the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Raleigh</hi> or one of the revenue cutters, it will be a good object
                    lesson, and will tend to have such people keep the peace.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Depuy de Lôme.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
